Vanessa says that you
are a photographer?

21:55.380 --> 21:56.813
Yes, sir.

21:56.815 --> 21:58.914
Just most family
portraits, mostly.

21:58.916 --> 22:00.784
Just?

22:00.786 --> 22:02.852
My family portraits are the
most mysterious and fascinating.

22:02.854 --> 22:05.721
Just think if those
photos could speak up.

22:05.723 --> 22:06.724
Yeah, that's true.

22:08.026 --> 22:08.994
Are you Lutheran?

22:10.028 --> 22:11.661
Lutheran...

22:11.663 --> 22:14.698
Were you at least
baptized as an infant,

22:14.700 --> 22:16.333
or were you dipped?

22:16.335 --> 22:18.834
Mama, could you come
with me in the kitchen?

22:18.836 --> 22:22.338
I was just getting to know
Vanessa's new little friend.

22:22.340 --> 22:24.341
My grandma has been
trying to set me up

22:24.343 --> 22:26.976
with her church organist
for like three years.

22:26.978 --> 22:28.611
And?

22:28.613 --> 22:30.846
Well, he's 40
and really creepy.

22:30.848 --> 22:33.382
Hey, but at least
he's a Lutheran.

22:33.384 --> 22:34.385
Yeah, that's true.

22:39.758 --> 22:41.357
Whatever.

22:41.359 --> 22:43.759
That is JP, my
parents' foster kid,

22:43.761 --> 22:45.496
and he is such a jerk.

22:46.998 --> 22:48.797
Says a lot about your parents.

22:48.799 --> 22:51.668
Yeah. Well my dad, his
mom died when he was 15.

22:51.670 --> 22:53.772
He was basically
alone from then on.

22:56.842 --> 22:58.641
You're putting too
much on the plate.

22:58.643 --> 23:00.709
You're doing a great job.

23:00.711 --> 23:02.010
- They'll fall off.
- Mama, come on.

23:02.012 --> 23:06.048
- Come on, mama.
- Oh, grandma, grandma.

23:06.050 --> 23:07.851
Put this right there.

23:07.853 --> 23:09.486
You do such a good
job with that.

23:09.488 --> 23:11.388
Eric, darling, can you
take the punch bowl

23:11.390 --> 23:12.855
and put it on the table and
then come back in and finish?

23:12.857 --> 23:14.524
You're doing a great job.

23:14.526 --> 23:16.426
Mom, oh my God.
These are so cute.

23:16.428 --> 23:17.559
You made every single one

23:17.561 --> 23:18.663
and you made the walnut ones?

23:20.565 --> 23:22.067
- I'm so sorry.
- There you go.

23:24.035 --> 23:26.469
You know what? I
think you missed a spot.

23:26.471 --> 23:27.970
Shut up.

23:27.972 --> 23:29.538
Here, I grabbed one
of my dad's shirts.

23:29.540 --> 23:30.873
You wanna give me
yours and I'll wash it?

23:30.875 --> 23:32.741
No, thanks. It'll dry.

23:32.743 --> 23:34.677
You're covered in punch
and it's gonna stain.

23:34.679 --> 23:36.078
It's just an old shirt.

23:36.080 --> 23:37.713
Eric, just change
your damn shirt.

23:37.715 --> 23:39.850
I don't need to,
so just drop it.

23:49.161 --> 23:51.126
Quieter out here, isn't it?

23:51.128 --> 23:53.062
Oh, I'm sorry.

23:53.064 --> 23:54.197
I didn't mean to scare you.

23:54.199 --> 23:56.132
No, I just got this new camera

23:56.134 --> 23:58.470
and I was experimenting
with the low light.

23:59.904 --> 24:00.771
Nice.

24:01.772 --> 24:03.172
Hey, come here.

24:03.174 --> 24:05.107
Let me show you something.

24:05.109 --> 24:10.115
Come on.

24:19.590 --> 24:20.590
Voila!

24:20.592 --> 24:22.191
Wow. This is great.

24:22.193 --> 24:24.494
Ed, I
need you for a sec.

24:24.496 --> 24:25.929
Oh yeah, Bonnie. Be right up.

24:25.931 --> 24:28.030
Here, make yourself at home.

24:28.032 --> 24:28.899
Okay.

24:42.513 --> 24:43.979
Where's Ed?

24:43.981 --> 24:46.149
I think he'll be
back in a minute.

24:46.151 --> 24:48.519
I'm Eric, Vanessa's friend.

24:57.828 --> 24:58.696
No.

25:00.164 --> 25:01.965
So, are you into art too?

25:01.967 --> 25:04.566
I think it's
exceedingly lame actually.

25:04.568 --> 25:06.070
Except for photography, right?

25:08.205 --> 25:10.773
Here, let me show you
something pretty cool.

25:10.775 --> 25:13.711
This was a couple of weeks ago.

25:17.214 --> 25:18.082
JP.

25:19.884 --> 25:22.151
What have I told you
about smoking in here?

25:22.153 --> 25:23.688
We'll talk about this later.

25:28.660 --> 25:29.792
Sorry about that.

25:29.794 --> 25:31.661
JP's been a tough nut to crack,

25:31.663 --> 25:34.530
and today he disrespected
Bonnie and I snapped.

25:34.532 --> 25:36.533
I said some things to him I
probably shouldn't have said

25:36.535 --> 25:39.768
knowing his history,
and tried to apologize,

25:39.770 --> 25:41.938
but I don't really
think it was enough.

25:41.940 --> 25:43.940
Oh, it's enough.

25:43.942 --> 25:46.174
He's probably more
impressed with you now.

25:46.176 --> 25:47.776
Why is that?

25:47.778 --> 25:50.013
Because you made a
mistake and apologized.

25:50.015 --> 25:51.680
Sometimes that's even better

25:51.682 --> 25:53.183
than never making
a mistake at all.

25:59.257 --> 26:02.824
Got my first camera when
I was stationed in Korea.

26:02.826 --> 26:04.095
I just couldn't put it down.

26:05.864 --> 26:06.996
These are great.

26:06.998 --> 26:08.631
I do love art because I think

26:08.633 --> 26:10.333
it's one of the
few things in life

26:10.335 --> 26:13.201
that you really don't have
to understand to create.

26:13.203 --> 26:15.337
I mean, you can
have contradictions

26:15.339 --> 26:17.741
and doubts, insecurities.

26:19.277 --> 26:21.177
Vanna showed me some
of your photographs.

26:21.179 --> 26:22.245
They're exquisite.

26:22.247 --> 26:24.215
You have quite a talent.

26:25.083 --> 26:26.815
Thanks.

26:26.817 --> 26:28.817
Stu says you're
saving for college.

26:28.819 --> 26:31.254
You know, the US National Press

26:31.256 --> 26:34.692
has a scholarship
contest for photography.

26:36.327 --> 26:38.797
You should really consider
entering one of your photos.

26:41.199 --> 26:42.931
No, I'm serious.

26:42.933 --> 26:43.801
You should.

27:31.415 --> 27:33.315
I see the sun
struggling for attention

27:33.317 --> 27:34.985
through the trembling branches.

27:36.788 --> 27:38.856
And the cold wind whispers
our approaching fate.

27:40.290 --> 27:42.424
I've pushed the
envelope of propriety

27:42.426 --> 27:44.895
standing so close to her canvas.

27:46.263 --> 27:48.930
I'm captivated by
her colorful layers,

27:48.932 --> 27:52.701
her deep strokes are miniature
mountains reaching out to me,

27:52.703 --> 27:55.373
making valleys shadow
in the cool lights.

27:58.308 --> 28:01.411
But I'm a shadow too,
sewn to her feet,

28:01.413 --> 28:03.114
with her as she walks.

28:05.316 --> 28:07.784
And she talks to
me as if I'm real.

28:07.786 --> 28:09.419
Are you warm enough?

28:09.421 --> 28:10.452
- Yes.
- You're sure.

28:10.454 --> 28:11.787
Yes.

28:11.789 --> 28:13.221
But it's really cold up here.

28:13.223 --> 28:14.425
I just don't want
you to get sick.

28:17.162 --> 28:19.197
But my awkwardness protects me.

28:25.336 --> 28:27.003
And like her shadow,

28:27.005 --> 28:30.141
I fade and wish the
sun would never set.

28:36.815 --> 28:38.280
But if I confessed,

28:38.282 --> 28:40.951
there'd be no reason
to wait for a reply,

28:42.319 --> 28:45.123
knowing full well
this thing will die.

29:02.507 --> 29:03.472
Hey dude.

29:03.474 --> 29:04.341
- Hey.
- Hey.

29:06.044 --> 29:07.176
I'm done.

29:07.178 --> 29:08.844
You've written four sentences.

29:08.846 --> 29:10.113
That was hard.

29:10.115 --> 29:10.981
I need candy.

29:15.053 --> 29:16.486
Hey, you know, most guys

29:16.488 --> 29:18.353
that are trying to
avoid a relationship

29:18.355 --> 29:19.354
just ignore the chick.

29:19.356 --> 29:21.324
You know, stop calling.

29:21.326 --> 29:23.325
They don't run off to
a third world country.

29:23.327 --> 29:25.327
It is a bit drastic.

29:25.329 --> 29:26.929
It's not what I'm doing.

29:26.931 --> 29:27.930
And you need to stop
reading my mail.

29:27.932 --> 29:29.231
I thought it was mine.

29:29.233 --> 29:31.033
From Africa Water Venture?

29:31.035 --> 29:33.068
I care about
Africa too, you know?

29:33.070 --> 29:34.237
Shut up.

29:34.239 --> 29:35.105
What?

29:37.509 --> 29:38.910
So you leaving again?

29:53.525 --> 29:58.496
You okay?

30:12.277 --> 30:15.246
Do you actually
think these look good?

30:17.949 --> 30:19.915
What is the matter with you?

30:19.917 --> 30:23.385
I took a chance on you when
you didn't even have an address

30:23.387 --> 30:26.189
or a phone number to
put on an application.

30:26.191 --> 30:27.959
And I have been good to you.

30:29.827 --> 30:32.995
I gave you some amazingly
fashionable work clothes.

30:32.997 --> 30:36.565
I gave you 32 bucks
of my own money

30:36.567 --> 30:38.301
to sponsor you in that marathon

30:38.303 --> 30:40.536
for your little Africa thing.

30:40.538 --> 30:41.405
And why?

30:44.209 --> 30:45.076
Why Eric?

30:46.944 --> 30:47.611
Don't speak.

30:49.446 --> 30:52.480
Because you were one of the
best damned photographers

30:52.482 --> 30:54.517
I had ever seen.

30:54.519 --> 30:56.151
But lately, you are late.

30:56.153 --> 30:58.854
Your work has been
subpar at best.

30:58.856 --> 31:00.021
I mean, where is the art?

31:00.023 --> 31:01.324
Where is the craft?

31:01.326 --> 31:02.892
Steve, are you serious?

31:02.894 --> 31:04.594
You take pictures in a mall.

31:04.596 --> 31:06.362
Of people sitting in
front of fake backdrops

31:06.364 --> 31:08.029
like the grand Canyon,

31:08.031 --> 31:10.632
that we then Photoshop
the hell out of.

31:10.634 --> 31:13.436
What did you say?

31:13.438 --> 31:14.305
I'm sorry.

31:16.441 --> 31:18.274
I'll redo the session
on my own time.

31:18.276 --> 31:19.143
I'm sorry.

31:26.183 --> 31:27.050
I'm sorry, kid.

31:28.920 --> 31:30.385
You're fired.

31:30.387 --> 31:32.020
What?

31:32.022 --> 31:32.889
Yeah.

31:32.891 --> 31:35.259
F-R-I-E-D.

32:01.286 --> 32:03.151
There's a problem
with the well we built.

32:03.153 --> 32:05.153
It's contaminated.

32:05.155 --> 32:07.055
They had to shut it down.

32:07.057 --> 32:08.457
What?

32:08.459 --> 32:10.359
They can't do
that. They need it.

32:10.361 --> 32:12.361
It's contaminated by
some form of arsenic.

32:12.363 --> 32:14.162
That's impossible.
We tested it.

32:14.164 --> 32:16.632
Yeah, but Eric, contaminants
can migrate for miles.

32:16.634 --> 32:17.967
We need to fix it.

32:17.969 --> 32:19.604
There's no money to fix it.

32:21.105 --> 32:22.472
Donations are down.

32:24.308 --> 32:25.975
I can hardly even pay the
lease to keep our door open.

32:25.977 --> 32:28.046
We can't just sit
here and do nothing.

32:31.982 --> 32:35.217
They're depriving communities
of clean water because donors,

32:35.219 --> 32:37.219
governments and
nongovernmental organizations

32:37.221 --> 32:39.087
have built infrastructure

32:39.089 --> 32:40.724
and then just ignored the
need to maintain them.

32:43.961 --> 32:45.997
I know, I know. I'm sorry.

32:48.665 --> 32:50.134
Okay. All right.

32:51.501 --> 32:52.971
Yeah, thank you.

32:54.305 --> 32:55.173
I'm sorry.

33:12.222 --> 33:13.090
Eric.

33:15.326 --> 33:16.193
Eric.

33:18.997 --> 33:20.228
Hey, buddy.

33:20.230 --> 33:21.398
I'm back from Chicago.

33:24.134 --> 33:25.236
How'd the marathon go?

33:26.503 --> 33:29.171
Dude, you look like hell.

33:29.173 --> 33:30.375
- Are you sick?
- What?

33:34.378 --> 33:37.313
Hey, aren't you
going with Vanessa

33:37.315 --> 33:38.583
to an art party tonight?

33:40.351 --> 33:41.584
And you are a little musty.

33:41.586 --> 33:43.520
You might wanna shower it up.

34:02.773 --> 34:04.574
You look beautiful.

34:05.509 --> 34:07.709
Where have you been?

34:07.711 --> 34:09.710
I'm sorry I'm late.

34:09.713 --> 34:11.713
I've been calling
you for days.

34:11.715 --> 34:13.681
I misplaced my phone.

34:13.684 --> 34:15.382
And I came by, are you okay?

34:15.385 --> 34:17.385
- You don't look good.
- I'm fine.

34:17.387 --> 34:19.389
Sorry I didn't call you.

35:29.860 --> 35:31.496
I'll be right back.

35:57.755 --> 35:58.623
Hey...

36:05.596 --> 36:06.597
What are you doing?

36:09.599 --> 36:10.865
You smoke?

36:10.867 --> 36:11.735
No.

36:12.802 --> 36:13.735
Then why are you smoking?

36:13.737 --> 36:14.869
I don't smoke.

36:14.871 --> 36:16.572
It was just one cigarette.

36:16.574 --> 36:18.309
Okay Eric, what's going on?

36:21.244 --> 36:22.744
I'm leaving.

36:22.746 --> 36:24.579
Okay. Well, wait
I'll go with you.

36:24.581 --> 36:25.449
No, Vanessa.

36:27.585 --> 36:30.318
I'm going back to
Kenya, I leave Monday.

36:30.320 --> 36:31.188
What?

36:32.289 --> 36:33.356
When will you be back?

36:34.891 --> 36:36.726
I'm not coming back.

36:37.762 --> 36:39.394
You're kidding, right?

36:39.396 --> 36:41.329
I always said
I was going back.

36:41.331 --> 36:42.597
Yeah, for like a little
mission trip or something.

36:42.599 --> 36:44.233
Not to go there indefinitely.

36:44.235 --> 36:46.702
And what, you're
going in two days?

36:46.704 --> 36:48.639
- Where's the fire?
- It hasn't rained.

36:49.706 --> 36:51.340
There's no water.

36:51.342 --> 36:53.275
The villages are waste
and full of disease-

36:53.277 --> 36:54.709
- So I'm a horrible person
for not wanting you to go?

36:54.711 --> 36:56.746
'cause I thought
that you and I...

36:59.282 --> 37:00.749
So what? This it, huh?

37:00.751 --> 37:02.351
I'm just gonna get like
a Christmas form letter

37:02.353 --> 37:03.251
from you once a
year, and that's it?

37:03.253 --> 37:04.286
Vanessa...

37:04.288 --> 37:05.954
No.

37:05.956 --> 37:07.590
Have I been huffing spray
paint this entire time

37:07.592 --> 37:08.757
or have you almost
been pretending

37:08.759 --> 37:10.358
like there's not something

37:10.360 --> 37:13.830
not going on between
us, on purpose?

37:18.369 --> 37:22.271
Just because I'm leaving
doesn't mean that I don't...

37:22.273 --> 37:23.271
This isn't easy.

37:23.273 --> 37:24.706
What it isn't easy?

37:24.708 --> 37:25.609
Tell me the truth.

37:33.684 --> 37:35.553
It never would've
worked between us.

38:33.443 --> 38:35.846
What if we're longing
for day to break

38:37.581 --> 38:40.617
but night has already
strangled the dawn in her bed?

38:43.086 --> 38:46.389
What if hope is just a
tale we tell ourselves

38:47.791 --> 38:49.626
and there's nothing
else to hold on to?

38:52.530 --> 38:54.765
I came to this place
to feel normal,

38:56.634 --> 38:59.637
but someone is still
pressing me down on my back.

39:02.639 --> 39:04.442
My mind is throbbing,

39:05.809 --> 39:07.110
my hands weakening,

39:09.512 --> 39:11.614
and my pictures
are slipping away.

39:42.545 --> 39:44.445
Hey, Eric.

39:44.447 --> 39:47.148
You know I'm surprised to
see you sleeping on the job.

39:47.150 --> 39:48.818
Eric, are you okay?

39:49.753 --> 39:51.820
Eric, are you okay?

39:51.822 --> 39:52.688
Come, can you get up?

39:52.690 --> 39:53.824
Yeah.

39:56.159 --> 39:58.092
Okay, just lie back.

39:59.697 --> 40:00.829
I can't
move. I can't move.

40:00.831 --> 40:02.463
Okay Eric, don't worry.

40:02.465 --> 40:03.898
We're going to get
you to a doctor.

40:03.900 --> 40:04.833
It's okay. We're going
to get you to a doctor.

40:17.947 --> 40:19.182
How are you feeling?

40:20.684 --> 40:21.552
Better.

40:22.820 --> 40:23.653
Thank you.

40:26.891 --> 40:29.992
Eric, arrangements
have been made for you

40:29.994 --> 40:32.661
to be sent home.

40:32.663 --> 40:33.664
No, no, no.

40:34.898 --> 40:35.833
I'll be fine here.

40:37.635 --> 40:39.635
Look, I will be very
sorry to see you go,

40:39.637 --> 40:42.003
but our doctor is very concerned

40:42.005 --> 40:43.871
at how weak you still are.

40:43.873 --> 40:46.175
American hospitals can help
you much more than we can here.

40:46.177 --> 40:47.675
No, no, Matua.

40:47.677 --> 40:48.545
Please.

40:50.447 --> 40:51.114
I need to stay.

40:53.617 --> 40:58.622
I'm begging you.

41:14.103 --> 41:16.804
You clicked like,
and then all of a sudden,

41:16.806 --> 41:18.740
you was talking about
some matters of the heart

41:18.742 --> 41:20.175
on his status.

41:20.177 --> 41:21.876
What, you aren't fucking
lying to me right now.

41:21.878 --> 41:23.144
No, this bitch.

41:23.146 --> 41:25.682
She's got too much respect...

41:42.833 --> 41:44.034
I don't understand.

41:46.637 --> 41:49.003
Basically, your
immune system thinks

41:49.005 --> 41:52.076
your spinal cord has an
infection, even though it doesn't.

41:53.510 --> 41:55.177
So it's making antibodies

41:55.179 --> 41:58.112
that are attacking the myelin
cells of your optic nerve

41:58.114 --> 42:00.016
and your healthy spinal cord.

42:01.985 --> 42:05.052
Eric, we don't know
exactly what causes this

42:05.054 --> 42:06.623
and it's very rare,

42:08.224 --> 42:10.760
but there's nothing you
could've done to prevent it.

42:15.164 --> 42:16.699
What's gonna happen to me?

43:06.884 --> 43:08.717
A household water heater

43:08.719 --> 43:10.818
can boil hundreds of gallons
of water a day, right?

43:10.820 --> 43:12.854
But this wouldn't be an
ordinary gravity filter.

43:12.856 --> 43:13.991
I mean, this would...

43:15.259 --> 43:16.624
Hello.

43:16.626 --> 43:18.025
I'm sorry.

43:18.027 --> 43:19.760
This wouldn't be an
ordinary gravity filter.

43:19.762 --> 43:21.195
You could use the pumps

43:21.197 --> 43:22.966
to force the water
through the filter.

43:24.934 --> 43:28.202
I know, but I'm
not a scientist...

43:28.204 --> 43:29.873
Okay, I understand.

44:21.992 --> 44:22.858
Oh God.

44:22.860 --> 44:24.092
Oh God, help me.

44:24.094 --> 44:25.362
Oh God, help me.

44:50.086 --> 44:51.853
This episode
was much more severe

44:51.855 --> 44:53.454
than the mild ones he's had

44:53.456 --> 44:56.958
and caused irreversible
inflammation of his spinal cord.

44:56.960 --> 44:58.793
Optica is progressing...

44:58.795 --> 45:00.996
He has some left arm paralysis
and right leg weakness.

45:00.998 --> 45:03.298
Optic nerve damage causing
significantly blurred division.

45:03.300 --> 45:05.766
Of a chronic pain and
become more disabled

45:05.768 --> 45:07.202
throughout his life.

45:07.204 --> 45:08.105
I'm so sorry.

45:25.155 --> 45:26.023
Hey.

45:27.724 --> 45:28.391
How you doing?

45:30.827 --> 45:34.095
The doctor said that
you've responded great

45:34.097 --> 45:35.030
to the medication.

45:35.032 --> 45:39.001
So that's great.

45:42.972 --> 45:46.210
I made some new
playlists for you.

45:47.777 --> 45:51.179
I'll just put 'em
on your table there.

45:51.181 --> 45:53.882
You know, you don't
need to feel weird

45:53.884 --> 45:55.383
or anything around me.

45:55.385 --> 45:58.820
Not that you would or
should for that matter.

45:58.822 --> 46:01.856
Besides, my mom already
bought you all this new crap

46:01.858 --> 46:03.358
from Ikea that she
made me put together.

46:03.360 --> 46:06.096
So you can't really
decide to move now.

46:09.900 --> 46:10.768
All right.

46:12.135 --> 46:15.170
Well, hey, I gotta
get going to class,

46:15.172 --> 46:18.442
but I'll stop by afterwards.

46:19.476 --> 46:20.344
Okay?

46:22.012 --> 46:23.144
Okay.

46:23.146 --> 46:26.884
Well, yeah, I'll see you later.

46:43.065 --> 46:44.065
Be careful.

46:58.148 --> 46:59.016
Okay.

47:02.820 --> 47:03.821
That's cool.

47:12.496 --> 47:13.363
I got you.

47:14.498 --> 47:16.130
Easy.

47:16.132 --> 47:17.201
Easy does it.

47:56.273 --> 47:57.173
Any change?

48:02.211 --> 48:03.644
I've been concerned

48:03.646 --> 48:05.012
because you skipped
several appointments.

48:05.014 --> 48:05.949
I'm sorry.

48:07.617 --> 48:09.251
I've just been really busy
with the holidays and all.

48:09.253 --> 48:10.918
I see.

48:10.920 --> 48:12.487
And how have you been adjusting?

48:12.489 --> 48:13.523
Just peachy.

48:15.358 --> 48:18.994
Eric, I would encourage
you to utilize the services

48:18.996 --> 48:20.631
that are available
to assist you.

48:24.568 --> 48:28.302
Now, it's a little trickier
with the blurry vision

48:28.304 --> 48:32.643
and the leg weakness
and the arm immobility.

48:34.244 --> 48:36.177
Thank you for that
comprehensive recap.

48:36.179 --> 48:37.345
Sure thing.

48:37.347 --> 48:38.348
Here you go.

48:45.489 --> 48:47.554
Okay. That's where we are today.

48:47.556 --> 48:51.492
Now, it's very important
for you to learn

48:51.494 --> 48:53.994
to do things for yourself,

48:53.996 --> 48:57.164
so you don't have to depend
on other people all the time.

48:57.166 --> 48:58.199
Wow.

48:58.201 --> 49:00.101
That was beautiful.

49:00.103 --> 49:02.539
I think I'll needlepoint that
and put it above the mantle.

49:08.177 --> 49:09.045
Shit.

49:10.313 --> 49:11.248
I'm reaching him.

49:24.728 --> 49:29.229
I truly believe that
I have the favor of God.

49:29.231 --> 49:34.101
And the good news is that
the Lord wants all of us

49:34.103 --> 49:36.739
to have thriving
and abundant lives.

49:38.608 --> 49:43.046
He wants everyone of us to
be healthy and successful.

49:44.681 --> 49:48.652
I have a vibrant life filled
with blessing I don't deserve.

49:50.454 --> 49:52.019
Blessing after blessing after
blessing after blessing...

49:52.021 --> 49:52.688
Hey.

49:54.557 --> 49:56.257
It sounds like God
is your trophy wife.

49:57.693 --> 49:58.561
Eric.

50:00.364 --> 50:04.365
Been a while since you stopped
by here to argue with me.

50:04.367 --> 50:06.266
Everything all right?

50:06.268 --> 50:07.769
Oh, you know, other than
having a fucked spinal cord,

50:07.771 --> 50:09.506
just living the dream.

50:10.606 --> 50:12.139
Spinal cord?

50:12.141 --> 50:13.009
I'm sorry.

50:15.478 --> 50:16.346
That's it?

50:18.248 --> 50:21.016
And if you need
His healing powers,

50:21.018 --> 50:23.017
just call on Him
and He'll be there.

50:25.355 --> 50:26.523
Amen and hallelujah.

50:30.659 --> 50:31.527
Oh my God.

50:33.063 --> 50:33.730
It's a miracle.

50:36.266 --> 50:37.200
Are you serious?

50:42.639 --> 50:44.041
How's it feel to get out?

50:47.510 --> 50:49.278
Well, feels good to me.

50:51.481 --> 50:53.380
Oh, hey.

50:53.382 --> 50:54.349
Do you mind if I say hi to
a buddy of mine from school?

50:54.351 --> 50:55.215
Go.

50:55.217 --> 50:56.383
Cool.

50:56.385 --> 50:57.385
What's up?

50:57.387 --> 50:58.519
Hey, Stu. How are you?

50:58.521 --> 50:59.521
How are you doin', man.

50:59.523 --> 51:00.356
Good to see you, buddy.

51:05.327 --> 51:06.262
How was Africa?

51:11.835 --> 51:13.135
I love your tan.

51:17.740 --> 51:18.840
Oh my God.

51:18.842 --> 51:19.709
Vanessa.

51:20.710 --> 51:22.209
Hey.

51:22.211 --> 51:24.545
How the hell are you?

51:24.547 --> 51:26.113
You know what?

51:26.115 --> 51:27.414
I would totally
invite you to join us,

51:27.416 --> 51:29.717
but we were just about to leave.

51:29.719 --> 51:31.788
No, I'm not
staying. I'm just...

51:33.690 --> 51:36.090
My roommate thought
she saw you here

51:36.092 --> 51:37.624
and I didn't believe her.

51:37.626 --> 51:39.661
What's happened to
you? You look awful.

51:39.663 --> 51:40.530
Thanks.

51:41.797 --> 51:43.130
I'm fine.

51:43.132 --> 51:44.132
How long have you been back?

51:44.134 --> 51:44.701
It didn't work out?

51:46.802 --> 51:49.336
Did you get my drawing?

51:49.338 --> 51:50.838
Oh, you know
what? That's my bad.

51:50.840 --> 51:52.173
Dude, I'm sorry.

51:52.175 --> 51:53.173
I totally forgot to give it...

51:53.175 --> 51:54.374
You gave it to me.

51:54.376 --> 51:56.110
No, I'm pretty
sure I forgot...

51:56.112 --> 51:57.547
No, you didn't forget.

51:58.681 --> 51:59.548
It was great.

52:01.117 --> 52:02.249
Yeah, well you
said you never had

52:02.251 --> 52:03.353
your portrait made before, so...

52:05.521 --> 52:07.690
Congratulations on
winning that scholarship.

52:09.726 --> 52:12.260
Your story and your
picture were really moving.

52:12.262 --> 52:14.896
Can you believe they called
him an idealist though?

52:14.898 --> 52:16.764
- This guy?
- My dad said

52:16.766 --> 52:18.635
it might open up some new
doors for you for photography.

52:20.170 --> 52:21.505
I'm doing some
new things instead.

52:22.672 --> 52:23.773
Yeah, I can see that.

52:26.208 --> 52:28.711
Basically you quit everything
when you get tired of it.

52:32.148 --> 52:32.815
Well,

52:35.784 --> 52:37.851
I never lied to you, Eric.

52:37.853 --> 52:40.256
And I really hope I
never see you again.

52:49.666 --> 52:51.499
I'm sorry, man.

52:51.501 --> 52:52.369
Are you okay?

52:55.838 --> 52:57.740
You told me she drew a circus.

53:00.409 --> 53:01.543
I'm sorry.

53:01.545 --> 53:02.646
I thought it would upset you.

53:23.833 --> 53:26.266
What the hell
did you do in here?

53:26.268 --> 53:27.969
She never wants
to see me again.

53:27.971 --> 53:31.305
And you, you wouldn't
want to either

53:31.307 --> 53:32.673
if you knew who I really am.

53:32.675 --> 53:34.275
All right, you're
talking smack.

53:34.277 --> 53:35.943
Shut up. I can't
even see shit.

53:35.945 --> 53:37.413
Hey, hey, hey.

53:39.983 --> 53:43.253
Do you know there are
millions of people

53:44.588 --> 53:49.226
who are at risk of death
because of drought?

53:51.628 --> 53:53.494
Good segue, buddy.

53:53.496 --> 53:55.599
But yeah, I think I heard
something about that.

53:57.266 --> 53:59.266
See, here's the thing.

53:59.268 --> 54:03.637
If I was God and I was gonna
drop a drought on some folks

54:03.639 --> 54:08.612
for the hell of it, I
personally would at least try

54:09.980 --> 54:11.845
to drop it on people
that could handle it.

54:11.847 --> 54:16.583
Not people that are
hardly surviving as it is.

54:16.585 --> 54:18.487
No, drunk man.

54:19.889 --> 54:21.021
Area's just prone
to more droughts.

54:21.023 --> 54:23.559
There's no cosmic conspiracy.

54:25.795 --> 54:28.262
And seriously, why do you
keep trying to believe

54:28.264 --> 54:31.634
in some supposedly omnipotent
being you don't even like?

54:34.471 --> 54:37.507
I was just trying
to be a good person.

54:56.293 --> 54:59.927
You're saying you want me
to record a message for Eric?

54:59.929 --> 55:02.429
Yeah, it's this new
thing that Eric's doing.

55:02.431 --> 55:03.930
He thinks that recorded messages

55:03.932 --> 55:05.867
are more personal
than written ones.

55:05.869 --> 55:06.800
Stu, what's going on?

55:06.802 --> 55:08.735
Nothing.

55:08.737 --> 55:10.606
Look, you said you didn't
ever wanna see him again.

55:11.675 --> 55:13.307
He looked terrible when I saw-

55:13.309 --> 55:14.508
- You know, well, time's
kinder to some of us.

55:14.510 --> 55:15.642
So I'll have him
give you a call.

55:15.644 --> 55:16.911
Stu.

55:16.913 --> 55:17.912
Yeah.

55:17.914 --> 55:19.646
Don't you have class?

55:19.648 --> 55:20.516
You know what?

55:21.583 --> 55:22.751
Seriously, what are the odds?

55:24.621 --> 55:25.619
You know...

55:25.621 --> 55:27.021
What are you doing?

55:27.023 --> 55:27.891
Nothing.

55:29.925 --> 55:31.559
Please stop leaving
your crap on the floor?

55:31.561 --> 55:32.793
Yeah, you're right.

55:32.795 --> 55:33.663
I'm sorry.

55:35.030 --> 55:37.030
And even if
you're on a diet,

55:37.032 --> 55:39.700
look at just some of the
great foods you can prepare

55:39.702 --> 55:42.003
in your new Showtime rotisserie.

55:42.005 --> 55:43.403
Hey, man.

55:43.405 --> 55:45.106
Hey.

55:45.108 --> 55:46.474
Anything good on?

55:46.476 --> 55:48.376
No.

55:48.378 --> 55:50.912
An eight-pound
mouthwatering pork loin roast-

55:50.914 --> 55:54.048
- So there's this thing
I need to tell you,

55:54.050 --> 55:56.450
but I'm not really
sure how to say it.

55:56.452 --> 55:57.851
You could just say it.

55:57.853 --> 55:59.686
Okay, brilliant.

55:59.688 --> 56:01.857
Just promise me you're not
gonna try to kill the messenger.

56:08.864 --> 56:10.399
Broski, you okay?

56:14.471 --> 56:15.670
She freaked, man.

56:15.672 --> 56:17.104
I didn't know what to do.

56:17.106 --> 56:18.438
You should have
told me right away.

56:18.440 --> 56:19.907
I tried, but she took off

56:19.909 --> 56:21.541
and I had to make
sure she was okay.

56:21.543 --> 56:23.411
What happened? Is she okay?

56:23.413 --> 56:26.012
I chased her down the street
and we went out to coffee.

56:26.014 --> 56:27.749
She was a total mess.

56:27.751 --> 56:29.717
I missed my class
because she was sobbing

56:29.719 --> 56:32.153
- for like two hours.
- I don't wanna hear this.

56:32.155 --> 56:34.054
No, no, no. It's a good thing.

56:34.056 --> 56:35.655
I think I helped her like
process it a little bit.

56:35.657 --> 56:38.793
I gave her like the
basic Wikipedia version,

56:38.795 --> 56:41.729
with maybe just a
little added commentary.

56:41.731 --> 56:43.664
You promised me you would
never talk to her about this.

56:43.666 --> 56:46.032
Dude, I promised that
like six months ago.

56:46.034 --> 56:47.635
Besides, I kind of
figured the jig was up

56:47.637 --> 56:48.936
when she was standing
at our front door

56:48.938 --> 56:50.539
and you didn't even notice.

56:51.907 --> 56:53.508
Shit man, I'm sorry.

56:53.510 --> 56:54.778
She wants you to call her.

56:56.980 --> 56:58.845
This does not go here.

56:58.847 --> 57:00.483
I had to change a light bulb.

57:13.195 --> 57:14.795
Whoopsie.

57:14.797 --> 57:15.731
I got it. I got it.

57:17.500 --> 57:19.666
I got a surprise for you before
I head off to the airport

57:19.668 --> 57:22.570
that might cheer
you up a little bit.

57:22.572 --> 57:26.675
So, I want to do our Christmas
gift exchange a little early.

57:27.876 --> 57:29.142
You're kidding, right?

57:29.144 --> 57:30.478
No, come on.

57:30.480 --> 57:32.447
I know that you're still pissed

57:32.449 --> 57:34.684
about the whole
Vanessa thing, but...

57:36.985 --> 57:37.985
What is that?

57:37.987 --> 57:39.122
It's a dog, homie.

57:41.056 --> 57:42.657
Chill out.

57:42.659 --> 57:44.592
That's not a dog.
It's a fricking hamster.

57:44.594 --> 57:45.927
No, it's a teacup poodle.

57:45.929 --> 57:47.461
Merry Christmas.

57:47.463 --> 57:48.896
Do you wanna hold him?

57:48.898 --> 57:50.764
Why the hell would
you give me a poodle?

57:50.766 --> 57:52.233
What do you mean? They're
like the smartest breed.

57:52.235 --> 57:53.633
Check it out. I already
taught them how to sit.

57:53.635 --> 57:54.635
Sit.

57:54.637 --> 57:55.670
Sit.

57:55.672 --> 57:57.472
Oh, look at that, huh?

57:57.474 --> 57:58.905
And his uncle's cousin's brother

57:58.907 --> 58:00.041
was like a poodle
state champion.

58:00.043 --> 58:01.943
I can't believe you did this.

58:01.945 --> 58:02.943
Don't worry about the
apartment's no dog policy.

58:02.945 --> 58:04.845
I talked to the manager.

58:04.847 --> 58:05.713
I told him you needed him
and he said it was okay.

58:05.715 --> 58:08.117
So I got you

58:09.552 --> 58:11.985
a bed and some food,

58:11.987 --> 58:12.855
and a bowl.

58:14.523 --> 58:15.557
I don't want a dog.

58:16.659 --> 58:17.527
Take him back.

58:24.967 --> 58:26.969
You made him feel bad.

58:29.606 --> 58:31.037
Hey man, it's cool.

58:31.039 --> 58:32.840
I never asked if you
were a dog person.

58:32.842 --> 58:34.010
I just thought that...

58:36.278 --> 58:38.679
Well, I'm sure I can find
a nice geriatric couple

58:38.681 --> 58:40.113
that'll take him or...

58:40.115 --> 58:42.016
I appreciate you
thinking of me.

58:42.018 --> 58:45.019
You know I'm only gonna
be in Aspen for a few days.

58:45.021 --> 58:46.987
My parents still
want you to come.

58:46.989 --> 58:48.523
That's nice.

58:48.525 --> 58:49.559
Thank them for me.

58:51.628 --> 58:54.831
You know, between my
classes and my internship,

58:56.632 --> 58:58.967
I'm not really gonna be around
a whole lot next semester.

59:01.871 --> 59:03.871
I should get going
to the airport.

59:03.873 --> 59:06.641
So what do you want me
to do with tiny Tim here?

59:06.643 --> 59:09.644
I mean, I'll take him
as soon as I get back.

59:09.646 --> 59:10.313
Fine.

59:11.914 --> 59:12.782
Okay.

59:14.182 --> 59:15.184
What's that smell?

59:17.286 --> 59:18.920
He took a dump in
my bed, didn't he?

59:18.922 --> 59:20.657
It's a good
thing he's small.

59:58.795 --> 59:59.662
Jeffrey.

01:00:03.099 --> 01:00:04.767
I can't believe it.

01:00:06.735 --> 01:00:10.271
I know I shouldn't be surprised
you're all grown up but...

01:00:10.273 --> 01:00:11.938
How'd you find me?

01:00:11.940 --> 01:00:14.143
The lady at the
library helped me.

01:00:15.978 --> 01:00:17.378
It was a little bit tricky
using your middle name,

01:00:17.380 --> 01:00:19.648
but I'd recognize these
baby blues anywhere.

01:00:20.983 --> 01:00:23.016
And aren't you the
good little Samaritan?

01:00:23.018 --> 01:00:24.686
And winning 10 grand to boot.

01:00:25.755 --> 01:00:27.220
It's just a scholarship.

01:00:27.222 --> 01:00:28.991
Who knew I'd raise
such a smarty pants.

01:00:32.094 --> 01:00:33.661
It's freezing out here.

01:00:33.663 --> 01:00:35.896
Are you gonna invite
me in or what?

01:00:35.898 --> 01:00:37.130
Fuck.

01:00:41.237 --> 01:00:42.905
Oh, look at the puppy.

01:00:43.940 --> 01:00:45.141
He's so cute.

01:01:05.061 --> 01:01:05.928
I don't...

01:01:08.297 --> 01:01:09.898
I never heard of that before.

01:01:12.068 --> 01:01:13.767
You're not...

01:01:13.769 --> 01:01:14.434
It's not...

01:01:14.436 --> 01:01:15.304
Fatal?

01:01:18.740 --> 01:01:20.208
No, unfortunately not.

01:01:24.947 --> 01:01:27.882
Well, no big deal. Shit happens.

01:01:27.884 --> 01:01:29.018
Yeah, it does.

01:01:46.302 --> 01:01:47.170
Here, let me.

01:02:02.117 --> 01:02:03.786
Nice place you got here.

01:02:05.755 --> 01:02:06.422
Live alone?

01:02:08.224 --> 01:02:09.092
No.

01:02:11.193 --> 01:02:12.929
You get a girlfriend?

01:02:13.862 --> 01:02:14.730
No.

01:02:19.835 --> 01:02:20.836
You get by okay?

01:02:22.304 --> 01:02:23.172
Yup.

01:02:28.143 --> 01:02:29.244
So are you clean?

01:02:34.884 --> 01:02:35.751
Yeah.

01:02:36.452 --> 01:02:37.420
A long time now.

01:02:42.891 --> 01:02:45.327
Well, I'm surprised
to see you here.

01:02:47.195 --> 01:02:48.297
Surprised?

01:02:50.166 --> 01:02:52.802
That a mother would wanna see
her only child after 10 years?

01:02:54.836 --> 01:02:55.505
It's 12.

01:02:57.072 --> 01:02:59.940
It's the day after my
13th birthday, remember?

01:02:59.942 --> 01:03:02.142
You got me a lottery ticket.

01:03:02.144 --> 01:03:03.278
Of course I remember.

01:03:05.114 --> 01:03:07.150
You just took off and I didn't
even know if you were alive.

01:03:12.355 --> 01:03:13.222
Anyway,

01:03:15.257 --> 01:03:16.458
I have to be somewhere.

01:03:20.061 --> 01:03:23.132
I'll come by again and
lend a hand or something.

01:03:32.440 --> 01:03:34.474
I remember being so sure

01:03:34.476 --> 01:03:37.078
that I had picked the
winning numbers for you too.

01:04:23.092 --> 01:04:24.293
Are you done?

01:04:30.532 --> 01:04:32.599
Hey, you stupid
dog, where are you?

01:04:32.601 --> 01:04:33.969
Come on, where'd you go?

01:04:50.018 --> 01:04:52.254
Get out of the road, you bum.

01:05:07.570 --> 01:05:08.905
Rough night?

01:05:09.972 --> 01:05:11.537
Oh my God.

01:05:11.539 --> 01:05:12.675
Where the hell am I?

01:05:14.010 --> 01:05:15.943
Hell's about right.

01:05:15.945 --> 01:05:16.612
Hey.

01:05:18.014 --> 01:05:18.681
What's your name?

01:05:20.181 --> 01:05:21.049
Amy.

01:05:24.686 --> 01:05:26.586
What's wrong with you?

01:05:26.588 --> 01:05:27.456
Several things.

01:05:37.266 --> 01:05:39.133
What?

01:05:39.135 --> 01:05:43.103
I was just looking at all
the religious books you've got.

01:05:43.105 --> 01:05:44.206
Yeah, it was a phase.

01:05:45.206 --> 01:05:46.141
You want 'em?

01:05:47.677 --> 01:05:48.544
Phase?

01:05:50.278 --> 01:05:52.681
So you're like an
atheist now or something?

01:05:54.684 --> 01:05:55.551
I wish.

01:05:59.454 --> 01:06:01.188
It's complicated.

01:06:01.190 --> 01:06:02.191
How can it not be?

01:06:07.262 --> 01:06:12.268
As for me, I definitely
believe in God.

01:06:13.068 --> 01:06:13.635
You do?

01:06:16.739 --> 01:06:17.606
Oh yes.

01:06:22.610 --> 01:06:23.545
I love him.

01:06:34.356 --> 01:06:35.224
No.

01:08:10.418 --> 01:08:12.251
Just a second.

01:08:12.253 --> 01:08:13.521
Eric, it's Ed.

01:08:35.877 --> 01:08:37.345
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:08:39.180 --> 01:08:41.317
Hey, I've been thinking
about you a lot lately.

01:08:42.685 --> 01:08:45.118
How much I miss
having you around?

01:08:45.121 --> 01:08:47.721
And not just 'cause you fix
things for me on the house.

01:08:49.524 --> 01:08:51.191
JP and I were thinking about
doing a little fishing.

01:08:51.193 --> 01:08:53.729
I thought I'd see
what you're up to.

01:08:55.296 --> 01:08:57.464
Oh, come on. I'll take
you out for an hour.

01:08:57.466 --> 01:08:58.799
I'll bring you back.

01:08:58.801 --> 01:08:59.667
That's it.

01:09:01.569 --> 01:09:04.571
I'm not really
feeling up to it today.

01:09:04.573 --> 01:09:06.540
I appreciate what
you're trying to do.

01:09:06.542 --> 01:09:08.808
Come on. You know, I
don't pull that crap.

01:09:08.810 --> 01:09:10.578
I just want to hang out
a little bit, come on.

01:09:14.350 --> 01:09:15.551
Who's your little friend?

01:09:16.618 --> 01:09:17.617
I'm watching him for Stu.

01:09:17.618 --> 01:09:19.318
Oh, bring him along.

01:09:19.319 --> 01:09:20.421
